Sentencas: The utilization of Carbon Nanotube (CNT) sheets as current collectors for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) was investigated in this study.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A direct spinning method was employed for the synthesis of the 15 & mu;m thick CNT sheet, which demonstrated high efficiency and cost-effectiveness.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The material properties of the CNT sheet were characterized as a cathodic current collector and were subsequently integrated into 500 & mu;m thick yttria-stabilized zirconia pellet-based SOFCs.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the SOFCs was evaluated at a temperature of 500 degrees C, resulting in a significant increase of 34.7% compared to the traditional SOFCs employing Pt mesh current collectors.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy (EIS) analysis was performed to demonstrate that the observed performance enhancement was attributed to a reduction in both ohmic and charge transfer resistance.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This highlights the potential of CNT sheet current collectors in not only decreasing ohmic resistance but also facilitating the reaction kinetics in solid oxide cells.
Titulo: Carbon nanotube sheet as a current collector for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
